help_explain:
This embed text contains all commands
Use `p!help [Command Name]` (without bracket) to see detailed info of specified command
help_bcustat_desc: Display user statistics of BCU server with percentage data. This command will show number of human, members, pre-members, bcu-pc users, bcu-android users
help_checkbcu_desc: Display users who have both member and pre-member roles or have none of them. Usually will be used for moderating server
help_analyze_desc: Must be used with attached pack.bcuzip file. Under construction
help_prefix_desc: Set your own prefix to make bot recognize your command
help_serverpre_desc: Set server prefix to make bot recognize user's command. Only **moderators** of server can use this command
help_stageimage_desc: Try to generate stage image if it can. It will use BCEN font images if it can as default. `stimg`, `stimage`, `stageimg` are also valid command
help_stageimage_argu:
`-f` : Force bot to use noto fonts whether it can generate image with BCEN fonts or not
`-r` : Generate image with BC image format
help_stageimage_exam:
`p!stimg -f Force to use Noto Font`
`p!stimg -r With Battle Cat's File Format`
`p!stimg -r -f Now with both argument`
help_stagemapimage_desc: Try to generate stage map image if it can. `stmimg`, `stagemapimg`, `stagemapimg` are also valid command
help_stagemapimage_argu:
`-jp` : Generate image with BCJP fonts
`-r` : Generate image with BC image format
help_stagemapimage_exam:
`p!stmimg -jp The Battle Cats Japanese Font`
`p!stmimg -r With Battle Cat's File Format`
`p!stmimg -r -jp Now with both arguments`
help_locale_desc: Set bot's language only for you. EN for 1, ZH (Chinese) for 2, KR for 3, JP for 4 (ZH, JP isn't ready). `loc` is also valid command
help_formstat_desc: Try to search unit with specified name, and display info of it. `fs` is also valid command
help_formstat_argu:
`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-t` : Display info with talents applied if this form has
`-lv` : Customize this form's level and talent levels. With order of `level, talent 1 level, talent 2 level, ..., talent 5 level`
help_enemystat_desc: Try to search enemy with specified name, and display info of it. `es` is also valid command
help_enemystat_argu:
`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-m` : Customize this enemy's magnification, can handle both hp, atk magnification. With order of `HP magnification, atk magnification`
help_music_desc: Upload music with specified ID. Can be used every 5 seconds. `ms` is also valid command
help_castle_desc: Upload castle image with specified ID. `cs` is also valid command
help_castle_argu:
`-rc` : Upload `Normal Stage` castles
`-ec` : Upload `Empire of Cats` castles
`-wc` : Upload `Into the Future` castles
`-sc` : Upload `Cats of the Cosmos` castles
help_stageinfo_desc: Try to search stage with specified name, and display info of it. `si` is also valid command
help_stageinfo_argu:
`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-st` : Apply star data
`-stm` : Specify stage map name to be filtered. Must be used after specifying stage name first
`-mc` : Specify map collection name to be filtered. Must be used after specifying stage name first
help_stageinfo_exam:
`p!si -s -st 3 DNA & DHA`
`p!si -s Eldritch -mc Extra Stages`
`p!si Jamaica -stm Itf ch.1 zombie`
`p!si -s -st 3 2-128-2`
help_formimage_desc: Try to search unit with specified name, and display animation image of it. `formimg`, `fimage`, `formimg`, `fimg` are also valid command
help_formimage_argu:
`-t` : Display image with transparent mode
`-d` or `-debug` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide frame of animation
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `Walking`, `Idle`, `Attack`, `Hitback`, `Enter`, `Burrowdown`, `Burrowmove`, `Burrowup` are only valid mode
help_formimage_exam:
`p!fimg -t Immortal Yukimura -m Attack -f 8`
`p!fimg -t -d high lord babel -m att -f 120`
`p!fimg flight unit r.e.i -m hitback` or `p!fimg flight unit r.e.i -m hb`
help_formimage_tip:
When typing mode, you don't need to exactly specify name of mode. For example, if mode is `att`, since `Attack` contains these letters, you can activate attack mode. Similarly, same for other modes, for example, `hit` can activate `hitback` mode

`-m hitback` = `-m hb`
`-m burrowdown` = `-m bd`
`-m burrowmove` = `-m bm`
`-m burrowup` = `-m bu`
help_enemyimage_desc: Try to search enemy with specified name, and display animation image of it. `enemyimg`, `eimage`, `enemyimg`, `eimg` are also valid command
help_enemyimage_argu:
`-t` : Display image with transparent mode
`-d` or `-debug` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide frame of animation
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `Walking`, `Idle`, `Attack`, `Hitback`, `Enter`, `Burrowdown`, `Burrowmove`, `Burrowup` are only valid mode
help_enemyimage_exam:
`p!eimg -t Curseblast Doge Base -m Attack -f 100`
`p!eimg -t 284 -m burrow down -f 5` or `p!eimg -t 284 -m bd -f 5`
help_enemyimage_tip:
When typing mode, you don't need to exactly specify name of mode. For example, if mode is `att`, since `Attack` contains these letters, you can activate attack mode. Similarly, same for other modes, for example, `hit` can activate `hitback` mode

`-m hitback` = `-m hb`
`-m burrowdown` = `-m bd`
`-m burrowmove` = `-m bm`
`-m burrowup` = `-m bu`
help_background_desc: Try to find background with specified id, and display image of it. `bg` is also valid command
help_background_argu:
`-w` : Specify width of image (Max 1920)
`-h` : Specify height of image (Max 1080)
help_formgif_desc: Try to search unit with specified name, and upload gif/mp4 of its animation. Once it's used, users can use this command after 30 sec or 1 min. `fgif`, `fg` are also valid command
help_formgif_argu:
`-d` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide end frame of animation
`-r` or `-raw` : Generate animation with mp4 format for high-res result. Cool down will be increased to 1 min. **Only Moderator can use this argument because it's quite heavy process**
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `Walking`, `Idle`, `Attack`, `Hitback`, `Enter`, `Burrowdown`, `Burrowmove`, `Burrowup` are only valid mode
help_formgif_exam:
`p!fg -d Cat -f 10`
`p!fg -r 493001 -m attack` [Mod only or `-r` will be ignored]
help_formgif_tip:
When typing mode, you don't need to exactly specify name of mode. For example, if mode is `att`, since `Attack` contains these letters, you can activate attack mode. Similarly, same for other modes, for example, `hit` can activate `hitback` mode

`-m hitback` = `-m hb`
`-m burrowdown` = `-m bd`
`-m burrowmove` = `-m bm`
`-m burrowup` = `-m bu`
help_enemygif_desc: Try to search enemy with specified name, and upload gif/mp4 of its animation. Once it's used, users can use this command after 30 sec or 1 min. `egif`, 'eg' are also valid command
help_enemygif_argu:
`-d` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide end frame of animation
`-r` or `-raw` : Generate animation with mp4 format for high-res result. Cool down will be increased to 1 min. **Only Moderator can use this argument because it's quite heavy process**
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `Walking`, `Idle`, `Attack`, `Hitback`, `Enter`, `Burrowdown`, `Burrowmove`, `Burrowup` are only valid mode
help_enemygif_exam:
`p!eg -d Doge -f 10`
`p!eg -r 535 -m attack` [Mod only or `-r` will be ignored]
help_enemygif_tip:
When typing mode, you don't need to exactly specify name of mode. For example, if mode is `att`, since `Attack` contains these letters, you can activate attack mode. Similarly, same for other modes, for example, `hit` can activate `hitback` mode

`-m hitback` = `-m hb`
`-m burrowdown` = `-m bd`
`-m burrowmove` = `-m bm`
`-m burrowup` = `-m bu`
help_save_desc: Save collected information to server directly. **Only Moderators can use this command because this touches bot's data**
help_memory_desc: Show bot's memory status. `mm` is also valid command. **Only Moderators can use this command**
help_idset_desc: Manually customize role to allow these users to use specific commands. ID must be passed as raw integer ID
help_idset_argu:
`-m` or `-mod` : Decide **Moderator**'s role ID
`-me` or `-member` : Decide **Member**'s role ID
`-p` or `-premember` : Decide **Pre-Memeber**'s role ID
`-mu` or `-muted` : Decide **Muted**'s role ID
`-pc` or `-bcupc` : Decide **BCU-PC User**'s role ID
`-an` or `-bcuandroid` : Decide **BCU-Android User**'s role ID
`-g` or `-getaccess` : Decide **Get-Access**'s channel ID
help_idset_tip:
If bot can't specially recognize server's structure, this server will have role called `PackPackMod`. Command which requires **Moderator** command will be able to be used only by users who have `PackPackMod` role at first until they manually set mod role id.
ID must be passed as integer value and each id must be set only once. For example, `p!idset -m MOD -m MOD1`, in this command, `MOD1` will be ignored
help_clearcache_desc: Clear all image link caches. (Bot caches all gif/mp4 which were generated by `p!fg` and `p!eg`)
help_animanalyzer_desc: Analyze custom animation files. Type `c` to cancel analyzing process or will be expired 5 mins later. `aa` is also valid command. **Only Moderators can use this command because this command can potentially cause internal error with misusing**
help_animanalyzer_argu:
`-d` : Enable debug mode
`-r` or `-raw` : Generate animation with mp4 format for high-res result
`-a` or `-anim` : Decide number of maanim files which will be uploaded, 1 as default
help_animanalyzer_tip: This command requires 4 things : Png, Imgcut, Mamodel, and Maanim file. If you upload one of these files, it will try to grab them and validate if these files have valid format. After getting all 4 files, it will generate gif/mp4 of analyzed animation
help_channelpermission_desc: Allow or Disallow users who have specific role to use bot's commands in specified channels. `channelperm`, `chpermission`, `chperm`, `chp` are also valid command. **Only Moderators can use this command because it touches permission of each role**
help_channelpermission_argu:
`-a` : Enable "Channel Allowing Mode"
`-r` : Enable "Channel Disallowing Mode"
`-me` or `-member` : Decide **Member**'s role ID
`-p` or `-premember` : Decide **Pre-Memeber**'s role ID
`-mu` or `-muted` : Decide **Muted**'s role ID
`-pc` or `-bcupc` : Decide **BCU-PC User**'s role ID
`-an` or `-bcuandroid` : Decide **BCU-Android User**'s role ID
help_channelpermission_tip:
This command can make specified role able to use, or not able to use bot's commands in specific channels. You can tell bot if you want to allow specific role to use commands in specified channels by calling `-a` next to command, or disallow them to use commands by calling `-r` next to command.

After deciding channel allowing mode, you have to call which role to allow/disallow by calling one of role arguments above, and then, call the channel(s) which will be allowed or disallowed.

Channel can be either mentioning or integer ID, and can set several channels at the same time

Moderators can always use commands in everywhere. If user has, for example, [Member] and [BCU-PC User] roles, and if [Member] role can use commands in #A, [BCU-PC User] role can use commands in #B, this user will be able to use commands both in #A and #B
help_formsprite_desc: Try to search unit with specified name, and upload raw image file of it. `fsprite`, `formsp`, `fsp` are also valid command
help_formsprite_argu:
`-uni` : Try to upload uni icon, aka deploy icon
`-udi` : Try to upload udi icon
`-edi` : Try to upload edi icon
help_enemysprite_desc: Try to search enemy with specified name, and upload raw image file of it. `esprite`, `enemysp`, `esp` are also valid command
help_medal_desc: Try to search medal with specified name, and upload info of it. `md` is also valid command
help_announcement_desc: Upload BC announcement link which lasts for 5 minutes (The link when you tap "i" button in main menu of BC). If argument isn't specified it uploads link syncing with user's locale. `ann` is also valid command
help_announcement_argu:
-en : Upload BCEN announcement link
-jp : Upload BCJP announcement link
-kr : Upload BCKR announcement link
-tw : Upload BCTW announcement link
